		<Tag>TXT_KEY_LEADER_CASIMIR_PEDIA</Tag>
		<English>[H1]Casimir III[\H1]
[BOLD]King of Poland[\BOLD]
[BOLD]Lived:[\BOLD] April 30, 1310 - November 5, 1370


	[BOLD]Background:[\BOLD]
	Casimir III was born in Kowal, at April 30, 1310. He became King of Poland at 25 April 1333, and reigned for 37 consecutive years, during which he built many fortresses across his kingdom, reformed  the law system, founded the University of Krakow, and most importantly of all, fought many victorious wars, Gains from these wars include a big part of Ukraine and the Duchy of Halicz. Also, noteworthy is the fact that he ptotected the Jews in his country, and encouraged those living in other countries to emigrate at Poland. Upon his death, at November 5, 1370, Poland had a much healthier economy and its size doubled. For these reasons, historians call him Casimir the Great.</English>
